  Clarifying Devnet Concepts\
  ### What is Solana Devnet and Devnet SOL?\
\
  The Solana network runs on three distinct "clusters" (parallel networks):\
\
  1. Mainnet Beta: The real-world production blockchain where transactions cost real money (actual SOL).\
  2. Devnet: A developer playground/sandbox. It operates exactly like Mainnet, but the tokens used there (Devnet SOL) have no\
  real-world value.\
  3. Testnet: Used mainly by validator developers to test Solana release updates.\
  Why we need Devnet SOL:\
  \'95 Smart Contract Deployment: Deploying our RBN registry smart contract to Devnet requires allocating storage space on the\
  blockchain. Solana requires you to pay "rent" (in SOL) for this space.\
  \'95 Transaction Fees: When the RBN node starts up and writes its Peer ID and IP address to the blockchain, it sends a write\
  transaction. Even on Devnet, writing to the chain requires a micro-fee of Devnet SOL to pay for validator processing.\
  Fortunately, Devnet SOL is completely free and can be requested from a faucet in seconds.\
  \uc0\u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \
  ### Step-by-Step Guide to Deploying the Registry\
\
  Here is the exact sequence of actions we need to follow to make this work:\
\
  #### Step 1: Set Up a Solana CLI Wallet (On your Mac)\
\
  To deploy the smart contract, you need a local deployment wallet.\
\
  1. Check if you have a keypair generated. Run:\
    solana address\
\
  2. If it prints a wallet address (e.g.,  4zMMC... ), you already have one!\
  3. If it returns an error or says file not found, generate a new keypair:\
    solana-keygen new --no-bip39-passphrase\
    This creates your default wallet keypair file at  /Users/dev/.config/solana/id.json .\
  \uc0\u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \u9472 \
  #### Step 2: Configure Solana to use Devnet & Request Free SOL\
\
  We need to point your Solana CLI tool to Devnet instead of Mainnet, and then request test tokens (this is called an\
  airdrop).\
\
  1. Set the CLI cluster to Devnet:\
    solana config set --url https://api.devnet.solana.com\
\
  2. Request 2 Devnet SOL (for program deployment):\
    solana airdrop 2\
\
  3. Confirm your balance:\
    solana balance\
    (It should print  2.000000000 SOL )\
